courses.description:
The course was created by Molfar's leading practicing researchers. Molfar is the biggest Ukrainian agency in the field of business intelligence, war investigations, training and coaching of OSINT specialists. Molfar provides expert material for The Times, VICE, The Guardian, Inquirer, Globes, CNN and dozens of most respected Ukrainian media.

This course is the only opportunity to see faces of our best investigators. Because there is a short wisdom: if you work well as a war investigator, it's better to hide your face. Enemies are seeking for Molfar's blood. But we keep on working, training and debunking terrorist's lies.

Advanced is a professional level of information search and analysis. Students will learn how to collect data as a real member of the intelligence services, as well as understand the principles of the investigation organizations, and moreover – get proven experience advice on how to optimize the running processes.

You will improve your skills in searching and analyzing information. In our course you will learn how to collect data like an intelligence officer. You will understand how to work in a team and optimize processes.

In the course you will learn to:
collect information anonymously by using social engineering;
analyze financial risks and origins of the assets;
test sites for unauthorized access;
find red flags and weaknesses;
master the methodology of information search;
learn how to compose data files properly and find blind spots.


Throughout the course you will have access to the case studies on how OSINT works and improve your search skills.
